<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,341,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Hypanus longus</emphasis>
(Garman, 1880)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1266,1941]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[541,752,1554,1580]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Longtail Stingray</emphasis>
. To about 
<quantity box="[871,955,1555,1581]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="cm" value="180.0">180 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[970,1050,1555,1582]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7805399999999998" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="70.1">70.1 in</quantity>
) DW (Weigman 2016). Bahía San Juanico, southern Baja California (
<bibRefCitation author="Fitch" box="[599,726,1590,1617]" firstAuthor="Fitch" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="539 - 554" refId="ref279031" refString="Fitch, J. E. (1953) Extensions to known geographic distribution of some marine fishes on the Pacific Coast. California Fish and Game, 39, 539 - 554." type="journal article" year="1953">Fitch 1953</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[776,871,1591,1617]" name="Ecuador" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and probably to northern Peru (
<bibRefCitation author="Chirichigno and Velez" firstAuthor="Chirichigno" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref270339" refString="Chirichigno, F. N. &amp; Velez D, J. (1998) Clave para identificaticar los peces marinos del Peru (segunda edicion, revisada y actualizada). Instituto de Mar de Peru Publicacion Especial." type="book" year="1998">Chirichigno and Vélez 1998</bibRefCitation>
), and Islas Galápagos (
<bibRefCitation author="Grove and Lavenberg" box="[582,891,1627,1653]" firstAuthor="Grove" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref284033" refString="Grove, J. S. &amp; Lavenberg, R. J. (1997) The Fishes of the Galapagos Islands. Stanford University Press, Stanford." type="book" year="1997">Grove and Lavenberg 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Benthic; depth: shallow waters to at least 
<quantity box="[1368,1436,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.18" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="118.0">118 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[206,276,1663,1690]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.179576" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="ft" value="387.0">387 ft</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Amezcua Linares" box="[298,564,1663,1690]" firstAuthor="Amezcua Linares" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref260157" refString="Amezcua Linares, F. (1996) Peces Demersales de la Platforma Continental del Pacifico Central de Mexico. Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologica, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico." type="book" year="1996">Amezcua Linares 1996</bibRefCitation>
), and probably deeper. Previously 
<taxonomicName authority="(Garman, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Garman" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[953,1311,1663,1689]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longa">
<emphasis box="[953,1122,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Dasyatis longa</emphasis>
(Garman, 1880)
</taxonomicName>
, we follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Last" box="[198,403,1699,1726]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Last" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="345 - 368" refId="ref293982" refString="Last, P. R., Naylor, G. J. P. &amp; Manjaji-Matsumoto, B. M. (2016 a) A revised classification of the family Dasyatidae (Chondrichthyes: Myliobatiformes) based on new morphological and molecular insights. Zootaxa, 4139, 345 - 368. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4139.3.2" type="journal article" year="2016" yearSuffix="a">
Last 
<emphasis box="[253,309,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(2016a)
</bibRefCitation>
and place this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1818" box="[801,901,1699,1724]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[801,901,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Hypanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
